18:         // parameters, but most of the time that map is going to be trivial:
19:         // argument 0 corresponds to parameter 0, argument 1 corresponds to parameter 1,
20:         // and so on. Only when the call involves named arguments, optional parameters or
21:         // expanded form params methods is that not the case.
22:         //
23:         // To avoid the GC pressure of allocating a lot of unnecessary trivial maps,
