ibility\n- Returns BetterResult.Left, Right, Neither, or Equal to establish partial ordering\n\nThis method is critical for selecting the single best overload from multiple applicable candidates.\n\n### 4. Conversion Analysis and Ranking (Conversions.cs, ConversionsBase.cs)\nThe **Conversions** class (inheriting from **ConversionsBase**) provides conversion classification:\n- **ClassifyImplicitConversionFromExpression**: Classifies conversions from specific expressions\n- Handles user-defined conversions, standard conversions, and lambda conversions\n- Supports nullable reference type tracking and recursion depth limiting\n\nConversions are used by BetterFunctionMember to rank parameter compatibility and select superior overloads.\n\n### 5. Best Type Inference (BestTypeInferrer.cs)\nThe static **BestTypeInferrer** class handles type inference when no target type is available:\n- **InferBestType** (line 51): Finds best common type for implicitly typed array expressions\n- **InferBestTypeForConditionalOperator** (line 116): Infers type for ternary conditional operator\n- **GetBestType** (line 177): Core algorithm that finds unique best type by pairwise comparison\n\nThis follows section 7.5.2.14 of the C# specification for finding the best common type.\n\n### 6. Supporting Data Structures\n- **AnalyzedArguments** (AnalyzedArguments.cs): Pools analyzed argument expressions, names, and ref kinds\n- **MemberResolutionResult<TMember>** (MemberResolutionResult.cs): Contains resolution outcome for individual members\n- **MemberAnalysisResult** (MemberAnalysisResult.cs): Stores conversion sequences, constraint diagnostics, and argument-to-parameter mappings\n- **OverloadResolution_ArgsToParameters.cs**: Handles complex argument-to-parameter mapping when named arguments, optional parameters, or params modifiers are involved\n\n## The Resolution Chain\n\n1. **MethodInvocationOverloadResolution** receives method candidates, type arguments, receiver, and arguments\n2. For each candidate, **MethodTypeInferrer.Infer** is called to infer missing type arguments\n3. Candidates are filtered by applicability (arguments match parameters)\n4. **BetterFunctionMember** is called repeatedly to find the unique best member\n5. For each parameter position, **Conversions.ClassifyImplicitConversionFromExpression** ranks the conversion quality\n6. If needed, **BestTypeInferrer** infers target types for array/conditional expressions\n7. The winning member is returned in the **OverloadResolutionResult<TMember>**\n\nThis pipeline implements the complete C# 7.x method invocation binding specification, handling generic type inference, overload resolution, and conversion ranking in a coordinated manner."
